ent need to rethink relationships between systems of government and those who are ‘governed’. This book explores ways of rethinking those relationships by bringing communities normally excluded from decision-making to centre stage to experiment with new methods of regulating for engagement. Using original, co-produced research, it innovatively shows how we can better use a ‘bottom-up’ approach to design regulatory regimes that recognise the capabilities of communities at the margins and powerfully support the knowledge, passions and creativity of citizens. The authors provide essential guidance for all those working on co-produced research to make impactful change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Civics & Citizenship.2bisacsh1 aAndrews, Heidi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBalla, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarke, Jenny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBond, Greg Leo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCantwell, Ari, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCheung, Makala, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCohen, Sue, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCole, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCole, Tim, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aElliott, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Nathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Penny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFacer, Keri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrayne, David, econtributor.